```markdown
# pi-provider-cloakbrowser

A [Pi](https://pi.earendil.works) custom tool provider that wraps [CloakBrowser](https://github.com/cloakbrowser/cloakbrowser) for browser automation via its REST API.

## Installation

```bash
npm install pi-provider-cloakbrowser
```

You also need the CloakBrowser binary available in your `PATH` or configured via the `binaryPath` option.

## Usage

```typescript
import { createProvider } from "pi-provider-cloakbrowser";

const provider = createProvider({
  port: 8080,
  host: "127.0.0.1",
});

// Start the CloakBrowser subprocess
await provider.start();

// Launch a browser session
const launchResult = await provider.callTool("browser_launch", {
  headless: true,
});
const { sessionId } = JSON.parse(launchResult.content[0].text);

// Navigate to a page
await provider.callTool("browser_navigate", {
  sessionId,
  url: "https://example.com",
});

// Take a screenshot
const screenshot = await provider.callTool("browser_screenshot", {
  sessionId,
});

// Execute JavaScript
const evalResult = await provider.callTool("browser_evaluate", {
  sessionId,
  script: "document.title",
});

// Clean up
await provider.callTool("browser_close", { sessionId });
await provider.stop();
```

## Configuration

| Option       | Type     | Default          | Description                               |
| ------------ | -------- | ---------------- | ----------------------------------------- |
| `binaryPath` | `string` | `"cloakbrowser"` | Path to the CloakBrowser binary           |
| `port`       | `number` | `8080`           | Port for the REST API                     |
| `host`       | `string` | `"127.0.0.1"`    | Host to bind                              |
| `baseUrl`    | `string` | `""`             | External base URL — skips start/stop      |
| `timeout`    | `number` | `30000`          | Default request timeout in ms             |

If `baseUrl` is provided (e.g. `"http://localhost:8080"`), the provider assumes CloakBrowser is already running externally and skips the `start()`/`stop()` lifecycle.

## Tools

| Tool                  | Description                                      |
| --------------------- | ------------------------------------------------ |
| `browser_launch`      | Launch a new browser instance                    |
| `browser_navigate`    | Navigate to a URL                                |
| `browser_screenshot`  | Capture a screenshot (page or element)           |
| `browser_evaluate`    | Execute JavaScript in page context               |
| `browser_click`       | Click an element by CSS selector                 |
| `browser_type`        | Type text into an input element                  |
| `browser_get_content` | Get page HTML, text, title, and URL              |
| `browser_close`       | Close a browser session                          |

## License

MIT
```

---

## Summary

Each file is ready to drop into a project named `pi-provider-cloakbrowser/`:

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `package.json` | ESM package depending on `@earendil-works/pi-sdk` |
| `tsconfig.json` | Strict ES2022 config, outputs to `dist/` |
| `src/types.ts` | All CloakBrowser API shapes and config interface |
| `src/index.ts` | `CloakBrowserProvider` class + `createProvider` factory |
| `README.md` | Installation, config table, usage example |

Build with `npm run build`, then `dist/index.js` is the entry point. The provider auto-starts the CloakBrowser subprocess, polls the health endpoint until ready, exposes 8 browser automation tools, and handles graceful shutdown on `stop()` with a SIGTERM → SIGKILL fallback.

