## Integration: CloakBrowser as pi Custom Tool Provider

**Package:** `pi-provider-cloakbrowser` at `/Users/shivam94/pi-provider-cloakbrowser/`

### Architecture

```
┌──────────────┐    REST API (fetch)    ┌────────────────┐    CDP/W S    ┌──────────┐
│  pi Agent     │ ◄──────────────────► │  pi-provider-   │ ──────────►  │ Chrome   │
│  (LLM + tools) │                      │  cloakbrowser   │             │ Instance │
└──────────────┘                       │  (ToolProvider)  │             └──────────┘
                                        │                  │
                                        │  manages ┌──────┴──────┐
                                        │  subproc │ CloakBrowser │
                                        │          │ (Go binary)  │
                                        │          └─────────────┘
                                        └─────────────────────────┘
```

### 8 Tools Exposed

| Tool | What it does | Key params |
|---|---|---|
| `browser_launch` | Launch browser instance | `headless`, `proxy`, `viewport`, `userAgent` |
| `browser_navigate` | Go to URL | `sessionId`, `url`, `waitUntil` |
| `browser_screenshot` | Take screenshot (returns base64 image) | `sessionId`, `selector`, `fullPage` |
| `browser_evaluate` | Execute JS in page | `sessionId`, `script` |
| `browser_click` | Click element by CSS selector | `sessionId`, `selector` |
| `browser_type` | Type into input | `sessionId`, `selector`, `text`, `delay` |
| `browser_get_content` | Get page HTML/text/title/URL | `sessionId` |
| `browser_close` | Close session | `sessionId` |

